614
01:31:26.854 --> 01:31:37.494
Incoming livestream: You might not have the full territory, but these landmarks are real. And what I do, and what many researchers do, is to use Apple's open source as a reference while working with the proprietary binaries.


615
01:31:37.494 --> 01:31:47.323
Incoming livestream: You'll take a binary, like launchD, syslog D, or a driver, and you'll use whatever logs or sources exist to match known functions, annotate call patterns, and reverse unknown logic.


616
01:31:47.634 --> 01:31:52.694
Incoming livestream: The agent angle is simple. This hybrid method is effective, but doesn't scale.


617
01:31:52.924 --> 01:32:01.324
Incoming livestream: Agents can do the repetitive steps, so correlate symbols, chase string anchors, retrieve relevant source context, and produce structured summaries that make a human reviewer better


618
01:32:01.514 --> 01:32:03.484
Incoming livestream: Faster and more consistent.


619
01:32:04.334 --> 01:32:21.134
Incoming livestream: Even when symbols are stripped, structure plus string constants plus syscall usage lets you map back to open source code, and four common tools show up constantly. So, like, strings gives you debug messages, format strings, and file paths, what can extract version and project info.


620
01:32:21.224 --> 01:32:33.414
Incoming livestream: Then there's NM, which will list symbol names if they exist, especially in unscript binaries or frameworks. And then ClassDump is great for interface information, especially, like, private frameworks and objective-C method surfaces.


621
01:32:33.654 --> 01:32:47.594
Incoming livestream: And when I'm trying to map binaries back to source projects, I also use Apple's distribution manifests to cross-reference components per release. I look at the release metadata when it exists, and I look for version strings or source file names via strings or what.


622
01:32:48.334 --> 01:32:55.804
Incoming livestream: All of these repetitive but context-dependent steps are the exact operations I hand to agents as tools.


623
01:32:55.944 --> 01:33:07.193
