01:35:31.564 --> 01:35:34.114
Incoming livestream: First, I use an agent pipeline approach.


639
01:35:34.414 --> 01:35:49.583
Incoming livestream: This means that I am utilizing a coordinated set of tool-using agents that turns raw inputs, in this case diffs, binaries, and logs, into evidence-backed outputs like, ranked triage queues, hypotheses, and buzz-slash-telemetry plans.


640
01:35:49.714 --> 01:36:02.724
Incoming livestream: I start by using a retriever. This is the indexing layer that searches embedded information like OSS code, symbols, notes, and log templates to return the most relevant context for a given question or artifact.


641
01:36:02.834 --> 01:36:19.203
Incoming livestream: And then I use a toolbox, which is like a curated set of deterministic analyzers and system commands, like strings, OTool, class dump, and log queries. The agent calls to gather facts and generate evidence instead of guessing. Then, more agents handle it.


642
01:36:19.204 --> 01:36:24.803
Incoming livestream: I use different agents for diff triage, RE context, hypothesizing, planning, and analysis.


